%md 
# File conversion

In order to convert the file to a column based structured parquet file, we match a regexp, the unzipping (.gz) is handled natively by spark, the regexp being greedy and buggy we filter big lines (> 2000 char) mostly articleBody vectors or the like. we loose some information there but avoid as well a lot of noise. 


### REGEX

The regular expression capture 4 groups Some filtering needs to be done afterwards.


### Writing result

Results get written to parquet by the cluster without going through driver program.

val uri = """(<[^\s]+>)\s+\.$""".r
val urlToTest = spark.read.textFile("urlToTest").orderBy("value").collect

    spark.read.textFile("open-data-plus/dump/daily2/*gz")
        .filter( line => uri.findFirstMatchIn(line) match {
                case Some(m) =>
                    urlToTest.contains(m.group(1))
                case None =>
                    false
            })
        .repartition(1)
        .write
        .mode("append")
        .text("ofInterest.gz")

import scala.util.matching.Regex
import java.io.File
import net.sansa_stack.rdf.spark.io.NTripleReader
import org.apache.jena.riot.lang.PipedRDFIterator
import org.apache.jena.riot.lang.PipedQuadsStream
import org.apache.jena.riot.RDFDataMgr
import org.apache.jena.riot.Lang
import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream
import org.apache.jena.sparql.core.Quad
implicit val myObjEncoder = org.apache.spark.sql.Encoders.kryo[org.apache.jena.sparql.core.Quad]
implicit val myObjEncoder2 = org.apache.spark.sql.Encoders.kryo[org.apache.jena.graph.Triple]
//import net.sansa_stack.rdf.spark.io.JenaKryoSerializers
import spark.implicits._


val rdd = spark.read.textFile("open-data-plus/dump/dpef.html-microdata.nq-00005.gz"); 
//rdd.show(10)

def jenaQuad(s:String) : org.apache.jena.sparql.core.Quad = {
    try
    {
        val it2 = new PipedRDFIterator[org.apache.jena.sparql.core.Quad]
        
        RDFDataMgr.parse(
        	new PipedQuadsStream(it2), 
        	new ByteArrayInputStream(s.getBytes), 
        	null, 
        	Lang.NQUADS)
        it2.next()
    } 
    catch
    {
      case unknown : Throwable => println("exception: " + unknown)
      null
    }
    finally{
        
    }
}

val quad = rdd.map(jenaQuad(_)).persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK_SER)
quad.map(_.toString).show
quad.take(10).map(_.toString).foreach(println(_))

import org.apache.jena.rdf.model.Model
import org.apache.jena.rdf.model.ModelFactory
import org.apache.jena.graph.Factory

import org.apache.jena.rdf.model.impl.StatementImpl

def jenaModels(quads: Iterator[org.apache.jena.sparql.core.Quad]) : org.apache.jena.graph.Graph = {
    try
    {
        println("sdf")
        val model = ModelFactory.createOntologyModel()
        val graph = Factory.createDefaultGraph();
        quads.toList
            .map(_.asTriple)
            .foreach(graph.add(_))
        println(graph)
        graph
    } 
    catch
    {
      case unknown : Throwable => println("   jenaModels  exception: " + unknown)
      null
    }
}

quad.map(_.getPredicate.toString).show(false)
quad.filter(_.getGraph == null ).show
val keyed = quad.groupByKey(_.getGraph.toString)
keyed.keys.show
val kc = keyed.count
val keyedToTriple = keyed.mapGroups((n,qList) => jenaModels(qList))
keyedToTriple.count
